This game is pretty fun, but with my Samsung s5, I've had some trouble with the gameplay.  Every time nightfall comes, it runs really slow.  It's also very difficult to play as the eagle, but even finding mates for the lovebird and bluejay are also very hard.  However, with the bluejay, I somehow, became successful.  I found out that after leveling her up to level 22, other bluejays then started to appear on the forest region... the island that you begin on when you first start the game.  Bonding with them, is also a little tricky though.  They act kind of timid so they never stay in one place.  Though, they usually hover above the trees, or on the ground below them, you need to always remember to look above the clouds.  That's where they often hide.  I know, because that's how I was able to bond with one.  That's where I had to look.  As with the lovebird, I just looked for her mate, and found him one time, over on the jungle island.  I noticed that they first began to appear, as my eagle would continue to level up.  So, I eventually managed.  This game is very fun, and full of many wonderful opportunities to play as other birds.  I might have some trouble playing it on my phone, but to be honest, this has been the greatest bird simulator that I have ever tried!

Gluten Free Games have done it again. Another awesome game in the bag. I know earlier in another GFG review I said that Ultimat Cat Simulator was my favorite, but this one is turning out to be a VERY close second. :) Every single bird is beautifully done, and all the islands and scenery is outstanding. The fact that you can actually play as 12 different birds just blew my mind from the get go. There are only 3 coat colors for each bird species in the game, which while smaller than the usual amount of coat colors, makes it much easier to just level up to level 15 or 20 on all the birds but the eagles to have a nice modest flock of 3. :} I love all the different islands, especially the Snowy Island and the Tropical Island although the other two are equally as awesome and goregeous. All the different baby birds makes me EXTREMELY happy, especially the miniscule Hummingbird baby. I know this is REALLY much longer than it should be and there are WAY to many all caps word, (see what I mean?), but I just couldn't express my infinite love for this app in any other way. :) HUGE (there I go with the caps again XD) triple quadriple thumps up from this girl. :)

This game is great. I'm a fan of most of Gluten Free Games' Sims. Although, I have some issues with this one. Firstly, it lags at times. I'll be flying, then it'll start to lag. Sometimes so terribly, that I can't even move. Secondly, whenever I hold something, it makes my bird fly upwards. Even though I had no intention of flying up. And thirdly, I can't move the screen properly. Its like I have wet or sticky hands. It either doesn't move the screen, or it only moves half way around the bird. Other than those issues, its a great game. So many places to find nests. And along with that, you must find sticks rather than having a nest already built up for you. What's also great is that you can dig and shake bushes to find food, as well as swooping down on your unsuspecting prey.
